 as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Person-affecting&lt;br&gt;view&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+7+8+13+14+17]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;   66k lives-eq/$1k · 70% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up Wild insects (humane pesticides) · 29%&lt;br&gt;(Jan Narveson, Melinda Roberts)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot + suffering_focused + collapse_degrades_future + time_of_perils_exit + person_affecting_view&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Person-affecting population ethics: making happy people is neutral, so the astronomical case for x-risk reduction — which rests on the sheer number of extra future lives saved from extinction — loses almost all its force. Only the harm to people who exist regardless still counts. This is the standard premise longtermism&#x27;s critics deny (discussed as the key objection in Greaves &amp; MacAskill&#x27;s &#x27;The Case for Strong Longtermism&#x27;). It requires no_discounting_future_humans, the astronomical-stakes move it pushes back on. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 7 animals_matter_a_lot → 8 suffering_focused → 13 collapse_degrades_future → 14 time_of_perils_exit → 17 person_affecting_view" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylWWtv2zgW%2FSsXwc6unUkcyW8nmwEyjTNTbPpAmm4xaAqXlmibE0nUklIcT6f97XtISbZcK6hafylcSTz33HMfvGQ%2BHfh8xtIgeSZ9fnB6cHJC5%2BfndKuYiCiR5Cn21wo%2FlhHdpW3H7dJSqsB%2FEHxJS3fSnvQm%2FclgMpy4nYnbnbgDauhExuQOmgboLgLghdZpGCdCRuQtgHtKDsVMSW8hWGBg3VGbXJoxNWFLtpos0pBFunjRJhaJkAV6omXIlwuWFG96NEuTVPF8wSRkScLVZCmSxcQX2pNplIhoXnzep0iWn0%2B2VhdfDdbmcjg2CeTa5JB0OptxZZdLL9XcXzvQIU8GAYs1n%2Fh8rpjPdW5i%2FUmXEhHyiZxNYmDABn8Ua2xoh6daRhMGE56laHS2Go6ZtyC2EVJoYvR6lSzweyYCTgjX5rU%2BocQIxXxfH5HiiLGIuCapLJjix9CfhRz%2BCY3nyYJnofmXhqaRZzHO4E8YS20kXH%2BAtZHPgYhHQls0nbDIZ4GMOIVIoqBFH9c5Mn74aK