) · 29%&lt;br&gt;(Jan Narveson, Melinda Roberts)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot + suffering_focused + collapse_degrades_future + space_expansion_backfires + person_affecting_view&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Person-affecting population ethics: making happy people is neutral, so the astronomical case for x-risk reduction — which rests on the sheer number of extra future lives saved from extinction — loses almost all its force. Only the harm to people who exist regardless still counts. This is the standard premise longtermism&#x27;s critics deny (discussed as the key objection in Greaves &amp; MacAskill&#x27;s &#x27;The Case for Strong Longtermism&#x27;). It requires no_discounting_future_humans, the astronomical-stakes move it pushes back on. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 7 animals_matter_a_lot → 8 suffering_focused → 13 collapse_degrades_future → 15 space_expansion_backfires → 17 person_affecting_view" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJytWWtz2zYW%2FSt3PNtdybVkUrJe9rozTiy3mXXSjONspxNnFIiEJKxJgguQltU0%2Be17AD5ERfKYqfZLRiGJc88994EL%2BPOBz2csDZKX0ucHpwfHx3R%2Bfk63iomIEkmeYn%2Bs8GMZ0V3acdwTWkoV%2BA%2BCL2npTjqT3qQ%2FGUyGE7c7cXsTd0ANnciY3EHTAN1FALzQOg3jRMiIvAVwT8mhmCnpLQQLDKw76pBLM6YmbMlWk0UaskgXLzrEIhGyQE%2B0DPlywZLiTY9maZIqni%2BYhCxJuJosRbKY%2BEJ7Mo0SEc2Lz%2FsUyerzycbq4qtBaS6HY5NAliaHpNPZjCu7XHqp5n7pQJc8GQQs1nzi87liPte5ifKTHumYeXzCH2OYhCCTKfPuZ0Lx0j4UjLnSeMVgyLNEjdpWyTHzFsTWcgpNjN6ukgV%2Bz0TACUFbv9bHlBi5mO%2FrI1IckRYRLEllwRRvIQos5PBSaDxPFjwL0D80lI08i3EGr8JYaiNk%2BQHWRj4HIh4JbdF0wiKfBTLiFCKVgjZ9KjNl%2FPDJUDXL4TmcwsIHFqSc5MwirJOqbcFecJ3QNF1RasyYhZpXHTuldwslwph%2B4wHShtNbJf8D3Gz1z%2BM345uL2%2FElTVc05xFXLOHteFVkMPdFsiHTIV4eITuSjIxREkgW633kcZUYl0OpkK2lYjr7NpODxXEguG7Tu1XYDuQ8kgop1Pgc944oHvW%2BNC2WjdbI%2BYFevjqzX055wrK